Sentencas: BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 (x=0.2, 0.3 and 0.4) proton conductors were synthesized by a gel polymerization method, and the effect of indium content on the sinterability, microstructural and electrical properties were investigated.
Titulo: Effect of indium content on the properties of BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 proton conductor

Sentencas: The results show that the indium doping to BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 can reduce the sintering temperature (1450 degrees C) to obtain dense pellets, and the relative densities and grain size of samples slightly increase with increasing indium content.
Titulo: Effect of indium content on the properties of BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 proton conductor

Sentencas: The indium doped BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 leads to the decrease of lattice volume, which hampers the proton diffusion, and thus causes the decrease of the conductivity of BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 with increasing indium content.
Titulo: Effect of indium content on the properties of BaSn0.5Y0.5-xInxO2.75 proton conductor

Sentencas: The maximum conductivity of BaSn0.5Y0.3In0.2O2.75 reaches 1.08 x 10(-3)
